https://www.codewithharry.com/blogpost/lamp-stack-ubuntu-20-04  for install lampstack

for install phpmyadmin:

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get upgrade
sudo su
apt-get install phpmyadmin -y

press space key for selecting apache2 and then press tab key for ok.
press ok then press yes set user(sabbir) and password(password) then ok.

sudo mysql -p -u root
CREATE USER 'sabbir'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';
GRANT ALL PRIVILLEGES ON *.* TO 'sabbir'@'%' WITH GRANT OPTION;
exit

for install wordpress:
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-wordpress-on-ubuntu-20-04-with-a-lamp-stack

for permission:
sudo chmod 777 /var/www/html for read write

if plugin not install:
sudo usermod -aG www-data $USER
sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www
sudo chmod -R 774 /var/www
